# OpenE2EE — mobile/ios/Runner.xcodeproj — Xcode project internal ignores
# Sprint 3 §9 (dev tooling setup; release build deferred to Sprint 4+).
#
# ─── STATUS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For Sprint 3 the Runner.xcodeproj is NOT yet committed. The directory
# exists so that the iOS dev tooling layout is discoverable, but the
# project file (project.pbxproj) is generated by each dev's first run of:
#
#     cd mobile
#     flutter create --platforms=ios --org com.opene2ee --project-name opene2ee .
#
# That command creates Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj (and the Swift
# source files under Runner/). Once signing and provisioning is wired in
# Sprint 4+, this directory will be COMMITTED with its own team-shared
# pbxproj and xcshareddata/.
#
# ─── RATIONALE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Hand-writing project.pbxproj is impractical — it's a ~500-line NeXTSTEP
# plist with UUIDs for every reference. `flutter create` is the canonical
# generator. Committing the pbxproj before signing is set up would create
# churn (every dev's `flutter create` would re-roll UUIDs).
#
# ─── IGNORES (active once pbxproj is committed) ────────────────────
# Until then, nothing inside Runner.xcodeproj/ is tracked, so these
# rules only kick in post-Sprint 4+.

# Per-user Xcode state — never commit.
/xcuserdata/
*.xcuserstate

# Workspace data that is regenerated by Xcode on every open.
/project.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/

# Per-user schemes (team-shared schemes go in xcshareddata/, which is committed).
/xcuserdata/$(USER).xcuserdatad/xcschemes/*